<header>
	Read the writing task on the left and answer the questions on the right. In some cases, there is more than one correct answer.
</header>
	
<section id="body">
  <p align="left"><b>1.</b>  Who do you have to write to?<g id="t1">A.  a friend</g><g id="t2">B.  a relative</g><g id="t3">C.  a colleague</g><g id="t4">D.  an acquaintance</g><g id="t5">E.  a stranger</g></p>
  <p align="left"><b>2.</b>  What style of letter should you write?<g id="t6">A.  formal</g><g id="t7">B.  informal</g></p>
  <p align="left"><b>3.</b>  What do you have to do in this letter?<g id="t8">A.  make arrangement</g><g id="t9">B.  request information</g><g id="t10">C.  offer advice</g><g id="t11">D.  make a complaint</g><g id="t12">E.  provide information</g></p>
  <p align="left"><b>4.</b>  How many points do you have to coverin this letter?<g id="t13">A.  one</g><g id="t14">B.  two</g><g id="t15">C.  three</g><g id="t16">D.  four</g><g id="t17">E.  five</g></p>
  <p align="left"><b>5.</b>  Which of the following could you askabout in this letter?<g id="t18">A.  if the hotel has a swimming pool</g><g id="t19">B.  when the hotel was established</g><g id="t20">C.  how far the hotel is from the town centre</g><g id="t21">D.  what the weather will be like in August</g><g id="t22">E.  if they provide meals for vegetarians</g></p>
